Investigating the fields explicitly shows that the reconstructed schemas now hold metadata which was not there before
{code:java}
schema[0].metadata

reconstructed_schema[0].metadata
OrderedDict([(b'PARQUET:field_id', b'1')]) {code}

Yes, this was added in https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/f609298f8f00783a6704608ca8493227a552abab. 

I don't think this is a bug. You can compare schemas without comparing metadata {{a.equals(b, check_metadata=False)}}. Perhaps we could change {{__eq__}} to use {{check_metadata=False}} when comparing.

Another option is that we could change the default for {{check_metadata}} to {{False}}
